# Shopify Liquid 2.0 Theme Development Rules

## Agent Configuration
- Always use Shopify Liquid 2.0 best practices and modern architecture
- Prioritize performance optimization and Core Web Vitals
- Ensure WCAG 2.1 accessibility compliance
- Follow Allbirds design system principles from the repo rules
- Update all locale files (en, pt-br, es) for any new content
- Include complete solutions with all necessary files and dependencies

## Performance Standards
- Implement critical CSS optimization
- Use lazy loading for images and non-critical resources
- Follow mobile-first responsive design principles
- Optimize for Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS)
- Minimize JavaScript and CSS bundle sizes
- Use modern image formats (WebP, AVIF) with fallbacks

## Code Quality Standards
- Use semantic HTML with proper ARIA labels
- Implement proper Liquid syntax with escaping
- Create comprehensive schema configurations
- Follow Shopify's JSON template architecture
- Include proper error handling and fallbacks
- Write clean, maintainable, and documented code

## File Structure Awareness
- sections/ - Dynamic sections with JSON templates and proper schema
- blocks/ - Reusable block components with validation
- snippets/ - Shared code snippets with performance optimization
- locales/ - Multi-language support (en, pt-br, es) with cultural adaptation
- assets/ - Optimized CSS, JS, and images with modern formats
- templates/ - Page template configurations following Shopify 2.0

## Design System Integration
- Use Allbirds design principles (minimalism, sustainability, comfort)
- Implement CSS custom properties from the design system
- Follow consistent spacing and typography patterns
- Maintain color consistency with brand guidelines
- Create reusable components following Allbirds patterns

## Accessibility Requirements
- Implement keyboard navigation support
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
- Include alt text for all images
- Ensure sufficient color contrast ratios
- Provide focus indicators and screen reader support
- Test with accessibility tools and real users

## Modern Shopify Features
- Utilize Online Store 2.0 architecture
- Implement dynamic sections and blocks
- Support app blocks integration
- Use metafields for custom content
- Implement advanced cart functionality
- Create search optimization features

## Development Workflow
- Always test on mobile devices first
- Validate Liquid syntax before deployment
- Check performance with Lighthouse
- Test accessibility with screen readers
- Verify all translations are working
- Ensure cross-browser compatibility

## Response Format
When providing solutions, always include:
1. Overview of implementation
2. Performance optimization notes
3. Accessibility features implemented
4. Mobile considerations
5. Required translation updates
6. Testing recommendations
7. File structure changes needed

